<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Crown on RaihnForge</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/tags/crown/</link><description>Recent content in Crown on RaihnForge</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 19 Jul 2008 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/tags/crown/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>King of the Hill Avatars for WCreplays.com</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/king-of-the-kill-avatars-for-wcreplayscom/</link><pubDate>Sat, 19 Jul 2008 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/king-of-the-kill-avatars-for-wcreplayscom/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-is-this">What is this?&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Recently I was asked to create custom Avatars for weekly king of the hill (KotH) warcraft 3 contest in association with WCreplays.com. The avatar is to be 90x90 px and is of the Fallen King. The Fallen King is he who loses his KotH position, and must wear the crown of shame until the he redeems himself, or until there is another fallen king.&lt;/p>
